## ğŸ¯ Why This App?

- **Bypass DNS Filters**: Works around CleanBrowsing and similar DNS-level YouTube blocks
- **Native Experience**: Feels like a real desktop application, not a web wrapper
- **Clean Authentication**: Handles Google login seamlessly via system browser
- **Silent Launch**: Runs without any command prompt windows
- **Stealth Mode**: Completely hides Electron branding

## âœ¨ Features

- ğŸš€ **Lightning Fast**: Direct YouTube access without browser overhead
- ğŸ” **Secure Login**: Authentication handled via your default browser
- ğŸ¨ **Native Feel**: Custom window controls and app-like behavior  
- ğŸ¤« **Invisible Launch**: Multiple silent startup options
- ğŸ›¡ï¸ **DNS Bypass**: Uses Cloudflare DoH to circumvent restrictions
- ğŸ“± **Responsive**: Optimized for desktop viewing experience

## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- npm or yarn

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/youtube-desktop-app.git
cd youtube-desktop-app

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run the app
npm start
```

### Alternative Launch Methods

#### Silent Launch (Recommended)
```bash
# Double-click start.bat for completely silent startup
./start.bat
```

#### VBS Launcher (Completely Invisible)
```bash
# Double-click YouTube.vbs - no console window at all
./YouTube.vbs
```

#### Development Mode
```bash
# Run with console for debugging
npm run dev
```

## ğŸ› ï¸ Build for Distribution

```bash
# Build Windows installer
npm run build-win

# Build for current platform
npm run build
```

